WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:19.602 --> 00:00:22.439 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Can't believe
it's already summer.

00:00:22.522 --> 00:00:24.941 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI pants]

00:00:25.025 --> 00:00:27.485 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Sakurai!

00:00:27.569 --> 00:00:30.196 position:50% align:center
[giggles]

00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:33.700 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] Well. Guess it's that
sweaty time of year again, huh?

00:00:33.783 --> 00:00:35.952 position:50% align:center
Maybe you wouldn't sweat
if you weren't so hyper.

00:00:36.036 --> 00:00:37.454 position:50% align:center
Hey, I had an idea.

00:00:37.537 --> 00:00:38.997 position:50% align:center
Yeah, what's that?

00:00:39.080 --> 00:00:41.708 position:50% align:center
It's just. I was wondering if I
could come over to your place?

00:00:41.791 --> 00:00:43.960 position:50% align:center
[grunts]
What? Again?

00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:45.295 position:50% align:center
Well, yeah!

00:00:45.378 --> 00:00:47.339 position:50% align:center
I can see you're not
grasping how committed I am

00:00:47.422 --> 00:00:48.882 position:50% align:center
to Uzaki Hills

00:00:48.965 --> 00:00:50.759 position:50% align:center
and the deep fear I have of
you building more without me!

00:00:50.842 --> 00:00:52.260 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
I so won't.

00:00:52.344 --> 00:00:53.470 position:50% align:center
Creepy old tower.

00:00:53.553 --> 00:00:55.513 position:50% align:center
Thing looks like an evil
emperor's hangout.

00:00:55.597 --> 00:00:57.724 position:50% align:center
Are you kidding me?
What're you talking about?

00:00:57.807 --> 00:00:59.559 position:50% align:center
Stuffed to the brim
with only the best!

00:00:59.642 --> 00:01:00.977 position:50% align:center
That's my dream house!

00:01:01.061 --> 00:01:03.063 position:50% align:center
So you're telling me
you'd set up a lava moat

00:01:03.146 --> 00:01:04.105 position:50% align:center
in your own house?

00:01:04.189 --> 00:01:05.690 position:50% align:center
Oh, right, that.

00:01:05.774 --> 00:01:08.818 position:50% align:center
That's so I'm prepared if you
decide to drop by and visit.

00:01:08.902 --> 00:01:11.738 position:50% align:center
[grunts]
Now you want to trap me?

00:01:11.821 --> 00:01:14.199 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Trap you? Ha! Get over yourself!

00:01:14.282 --> 00:01:15.533 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
I meant with the lava!

00:01:15.617 --> 00:01:17.660 position:50% align:center
Rgh. I hate it when you do that!

00:03:01.348 --> 00:03:03.016 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Crazy  cat.

00:03:03.099 --> 00:03:05.935 position:50% align:center
What the heck are
you doing up here?

00:03:06.019 --> 00:03:08.480 position:50% align:center
Don't worry,
I'm coming to get you.

00:03:08.563 --> 00:03:11.358 position:50% align:center
Just stay right there
and be a good kitty.

00:03:12.609 --> 00:03:15.820 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Almost got you.

00:03:15.904 --> 00:03:18.114 position:50% align:center
See? You're okay.

00:03:19.449 --> 00:03:21.201 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI gasps]

00:03:21.284 --> 00:03:22.243 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Crap!

00:03:22.327 --> 00:03:25.538 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI shouts]
No!

00:03:25.622 --> 00:03:28.458 position:50% align:center
[shouting continues]

00:03:28.541 --> 00:03:31.878 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI gasps]

00:03:31.961 --> 00:03:34.130 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Whoa. Was I dreaming?

00:03:34.214 --> 00:03:36.299 position:50% align:center
Well, duh, I guess.

00:03:36.383 --> 00:03:40.011 position:50% align:center
I must've nodded off,
then woke back up in a panic.

00:03:40.095 --> 00:03:42.806 position:50% align:center
That hasn't happened in a while.

00:03:42.889 --> 00:03:45.725 position:50% align:center
Man, I really hope
no one else saw.

00:03:45.809 --> 00:03:47.018 position:50% align:center
Uh.

00:03:51.856 --> 00:03:56.194 position:50% align:center
[grunts[
Seriously? Why is it always her?

00:03:56.277 --> 00:04:00.323 position:50% align:center
Stop! Turn around!
We're in the middle of class!

00:04:00.407 --> 00:04:03.326 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] Aw... Good morning,
Mr. Sleepyhead!

00:04:03.410 --> 00:04:05.036 position:50% align:center
Lemme guess, were you
falling in your dream

00:04:05.120 --> 00:04:06.538 position:50% align:center
and then you suddenly woke up?

00:04:06.621 --> 00:04:08.581 position:50% align:center
Cuz you totally jolted awake!

00:04:08.665 --> 00:04:10.542 position:50% align:center
Try not to nod off, grandpa!

00:04:10.625 --> 00:04:13.670 position:50% align:center
I'm so happy I got to
witness this moment.

00:04:13.753 --> 00:04:16.297 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
God, you are so annoying!

00:04:16.381 --> 00:04:19.467 position:50% align:center
Look, just shut it!
Class has started, okay?

00:04:19.551 --> 00:04:21.344 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Oops, my bad!

00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:23.388 position:50% align:center
How many of you are
familiar with the idea

00:04:23.471 --> 00:04:25.390 position:50% align:center
of dream interpretation?

00:04:25.473 --> 00:04:27.517 position:50% align:center
It holds that the content
of one's dreams

00:04:27.600 --> 00:04:29.436 position:50% align:center
reveals one's mental state.

00:04:29.519 --> 00:04:31.980 position:50% align:center
Dreams of falling from a
great height, for example,

00:04:32.063 --> 00:04:33.481 position:50% align:center
can indicate deep-seated,

00:04:33.565 --> 00:04:35.859 position:50% align:center
conscious or subconscious
feelings of anxiety.

00:04:35.942 --> 00:04:38.069 position:50% align:center
Aw, is somebody anxious?

00:04:38.153 --> 00:04:41.072 position:50% align:center
Don't worry. I hope you know
you can tell me anything.

00:04:41.156 --> 00:04:41.990 position:50% align:center
Safe space.

00:04:42.073 --> 00:04:43.491 position:50% align:center
Would you shut up?

00:04:43.575 --> 00:04:45.452 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE LECTURER A] It's also
common to dream of falling

00:04:45.535 --> 00:04:49.122 position:50% align:center
when one is in very high spirits
and maybe getting carried away.

00:04:49.205 --> 00:04:51.374 position:50% align:center
This can be interpreted as a
warning to put one's feet...

00:04:51.458 --> 00:04:53.501 position:50% align:center
Uh-oh, were you getting
carried away?

00:04:53.585 --> 00:04:55.962 position:50% align:center
Seriously, shut up.

00:04:56.046 --> 00:04:57.964 position:50% align:center
Hey! Don't get
too excited, okay?

00:04:58.048 --> 00:05:00.383 position:50% align:center
Gotta keep those feet on
the ground, my brosky.

00:05:00.467 --> 00:05:02.260 position:50% align:center
Look who's talking!

00:05:05.847 --> 00:05:08.725 position:50% align:center
Oh my gosh, the timing of
that lecture was amazing!

00:05:08.808 --> 00:05:10.477 position:50% align:center
It was so hilarious!

00:05:10.560 --> 00:05:12.187 position:50% align:center
Didn't expect to have
your deepest psyche

00:05:12.270 --> 00:05:14.773 position:50% align:center
laid bare in class, didja?

00:05:14.856 --> 00:05:16.358 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Whatever, I'm not a kid.

00:05:16.441 --> 00:05:19.569 position:50% align:center
I don't believe in
that stuff, anyway.

00:05:19.652 --> 00:05:22.197 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE LECTURER A]
Maybe it was juvenile.

00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:24.616 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] Well, I'm more
of a believer, I guess.

00:05:24.699 --> 00:05:27.535 position:50% align:center
Psychological tests,
blood-type fortunes.

00:05:27.619 --> 00:05:29.662 position:50% align:center
Pure superstition, all of it.

00:05:29.746 --> 00:05:32.165 position:50% align:center
That's not what actual
psychology is about.

00:05:32.248 --> 00:05:35.919 position:50% align:center
Sure. That's easy to say, but I
bet you believe it a little bit.

00:05:36.002 --> 00:05:36.920 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Nope, sorry.

00:05:37.003 --> 00:05:38.797 position:50% align:center
Come on,
psychologically speaking--

00:05:38.880 --> 00:05:39.673 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:05:39.756 --> 00:05:41.091 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:41.174 --> 00:05:43.301 position:50% align:center
Not good.

00:05:43.385 --> 00:05:46.012 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Watch out!
What are you trying to do?

00:05:46.096 --> 00:05:49.599 position:50% align:center
Nice catch there, buddy.
Oh, that was scary!

00:05:49.683 --> 00:05:51.059 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] That's what happens
when you're more focused

00:05:51.142 --> 00:05:53.645 position:50% align:center
on riling someone up
than watching your step.

00:05:53.728 --> 00:05:55.438 position:50% align:center
Mind your business!

00:05:56.564 --> 00:05:58.817 position:50% align:center
Huh. Just had a thought.

00:05:58.900 --> 00:05:59.984 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
About what?

00:06:00.068 --> 00:06:01.569 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
People who climb down stairs

00:06:01.653 --> 00:06:05.365 position:50% align:center
can develop climacophobia,
the fear of climbing.

00:06:05.448 --> 00:06:06.825 position:50% align:center
What?

00:06:06.908 --> 00:06:09.077 position:50% align:center
Wow, where the heck did that
come from all of a sudden?

00:06:09.160 --> 00:06:10.704 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
It's like an aftershock.

00:06:10.787 --> 00:06:12.038 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Oh yeah?

00:06:12.122 --> 00:06:14.416 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] It's commonly
known as "the stair yips".

00:06:14.499 --> 00:06:17.544 position:50% align:center
You'll just be navigating stairs
as usual when, one day,

00:06:17.627 --> 00:06:20.630 position:50% align:center
you realize you can't seem get
down them smoothly anymore.

00:06:20.714 --> 00:06:22.215 position:50% align:center
Or you tumble, until, at last,

00:06:22.298 --> 00:06:24.884 position:50% align:center
you find that you're terrified
of the very stairs themselves.

00:06:24.968 --> 00:06:26.511 position:50% align:center
I don't wanna hear this!

00:06:26.594 --> 00:06:30.265 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI yells]

00:06:32.934 --> 00:06:33.768 position:50% align:center
[GIRL C]
Aw!

00:06:33.852 --> 00:06:35.270 position:50% align:center
C'mon, why not?

00:06:35.353 --> 00:06:36.396 position:50% align:center
Hey!

00:06:36.479 --> 00:06:37.439 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:06:37.522 --> 00:06:39.566 position:50% align:center
'Cause I have plans
with that guy.

00:06:39.649 --> 00:06:40.734 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS growl]

00:06:40.817 --> 00:06:42.318 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:42.402 --> 00:06:43.820 position:50% align:center
Maybe next time, 'kay?

00:06:43.903 --> 00:06:46.406 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS]
Aw!

00:06:46.489 --> 00:06:49.034 position:50% align:center
Man. Good timing there, dude.

00:06:49.117 --> 00:06:50.660 position:50% align:center
They were relentless!

00:06:50.744 --> 00:06:53.538 position:50% align:center
Wait, what gives?
You running away?

00:06:53.621 --> 00:06:55.915 position:50% align:center
To tell you the truth,
I've never had much fun

00:06:55.999 --> 00:06:57.542 position:50% align:center
going out drinking
with that bunch.

00:06:57.625 --> 00:06:58.626 position:50% align:center
We just don't click.

00:06:58.710 --> 00:07:00.962 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Hm.

00:07:01.046 --> 00:07:03.840 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI] So many people
drink way too much.

00:07:03.923 --> 00:07:06.468 position:50% align:center
I prefer to be a bit
more chill. Heh.

00:07:06.551 --> 00:07:09.971 position:50% align:center
So sober me is usually stuck
cleaning up the mess.

00:07:10.055 --> 00:07:12.807 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Yeah. I'm not into that, either.

00:07:12.891 --> 00:07:15.935 position:50% align:center
Sakaki's getting away.
Aren't we following him?

00:07:16.019 --> 00:07:19.564 position:50% align:center
[GIRL D] Hmm. I don't know,
that other guy's scary.

00:07:19.647 --> 00:07:22.233 position:50% align:center
I get that. It's the eyes.

00:07:22.317 --> 00:07:24.611 position:50% align:center
[GIRL D]
Yeah, right?

00:07:24.694 --> 00:07:26.237 position:50% align:center
Those two are together
a lot, though.

00:07:26.321 --> 00:07:27.947 position:50% align:center
Must be friends.

00:07:31.284 --> 00:07:32.786 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
So, what's up?

00:07:32.869 --> 00:07:35.789 position:50% align:center
Kinda feels like I barely saw
you around at all last month.

00:07:35.872 --> 00:07:39.084 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI] Yeah. I popped
over to Okinawa.

00:07:39.167 --> 00:07:41.628 position:50% align:center
What? But we weren't on break!

00:07:41.711 --> 00:07:44.381 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI] Meh. I had a sudden
urge to see the ocean.

00:07:44.464 --> 00:07:45.965 position:50% align:center
Wow, must be nice.

00:07:46.049 --> 00:07:47.550 position:50% align:center
What about you, Saku?

00:07:47.634 --> 00:07:49.928 position:50% align:center
Anything happen
while I was gone?

00:07:53.682 --> 00:07:54.891 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Nope.

00:07:58.144 --> 00:08:00.230 position:50% align:center
Ah. I mean...

00:08:00.313 --> 00:08:02.232 position:50% align:center
No. Nothing.

00:08:02.315 --> 00:08:04.025 position:50% align:center
What even was that?

00:08:04.109 --> 00:08:06.277 position:50% align:center
This last month is kind
of impossible for me

00:08:06.361 --> 00:08:07.821 position:50% align:center
to put into words.

00:08:07.904 --> 00:08:09.030 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI]
What happened?

00:08:09.114 --> 00:08:12.450 position:50% align:center
Life! I mean, it was
basically normal.

00:08:12.534 --> 00:08:14.452 position:50% align:center
I went to class, went to work,

00:08:14.536 --> 00:08:17.330 position:50% align:center
did a lot of gaming
and stuff like that.

00:08:17.414 --> 00:08:19.499 position:50% align:center
I kept pretty busy, I guess.

00:08:19.582 --> 00:08:21.418 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI]
Stop! Can't you just let go

00:08:21.501 --> 00:08:23.712 position:50% align:center
and get a little wild
for once in your life?

00:08:23.795 --> 00:08:25.422 position:50% align:center
I've been hanging out
with you for three years

00:08:25.505 --> 00:08:28.258 position:50% align:center
and your life is so boring
I can hardly take it!

00:08:28.341 --> 00:08:29.801 position:50% align:center
You're a bummer, dude.

00:08:29.884 --> 00:08:31.720 position:50% align:center
You know we only get
four years of college

00:08:31.803 --> 00:08:33.304 position:50% align:center
and you're totally
wasting them.

00:08:33.388 --> 00:08:34.806 position:50% align:center
Find a girl, man!

00:08:34.889 --> 00:08:37.559 position:50% align:center
There it is. Why do
you always say that?

00:08:37.642 --> 00:08:40.729 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI grunts]
There's no time for drinking!

00:08:40.812 --> 00:08:42.856 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] What the heck?
Dude, you just gave it to me!

00:08:42.939 --> 00:08:44.315 position:50% align:center
Shut up!

00:08:44.399 --> 00:08:46.234 position:50% align:center
Idiots like you who waste
their youth are infuriating!

00:08:46.317 --> 00:08:48.695 position:50% align:center
--[UZAKI] Hey, Sakurai!
--[SAKAKI] Huh?

00:08:48.778 --> 00:08:50.780 position:50% align:center
There you are! I was
trying to find you--

00:08:50.864 --> 00:08:52.157 position:50% align:center
Who's this?

00:08:52.240 --> 00:08:53.950 position:50% align:center
Might this person be...?

00:08:54.034 --> 00:08:58.329 position:50% align:center
No way. Is it possible
he's your friend?

00:08:58.413 --> 00:08:59.789 position:50% align:center
Yeah, that's right.

00:08:59.873 --> 00:09:01.249 position:50% align:center
What?!

00:09:02.375 --> 00:09:07.756 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] So, wait. You're saying.
You really do have a friend?

00:09:07.839 --> 00:09:10.717 position:50% align:center
I mean, I know you
talked him up and all.

00:09:10.800 --> 00:09:11.843 position:50% align:center
Gotta be honest, though,

00:09:11.926 --> 00:09:13.970 position:50% align:center
I definitely thought
he was imaginary.

00:09:14.054 --> 00:09:15.430 position:50% align:center
What're you saying, moron?

00:09:15.513 --> 00:09:18.224 position:50% align:center
You totally saw me eating
with him in the dining hall!

00:09:18.308 --> 00:09:19.809 position:50% align:center
Yes, I remember that.

00:09:19.893 --> 00:09:23.521 position:50% align:center
I thought you were just
pretending he was your friend.

00:09:23.605 --> 00:09:25.190 position:50% align:center
Thank goodness!

00:09:25.273 --> 00:09:27.484 position:50% align:center
This knowledge makes me happy!

00:09:27.567 --> 00:09:29.861 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Wait, you were
seriously worried about me?

00:09:29.944 --> 00:09:31.613 position:50% align:center
Would you quit with that look?

00:09:31.696 --> 00:09:33.865 position:50% align:center
Oh, right, you're the same
girl I've seen with Saku

00:09:33.948 --> 00:09:35.158 position:50% align:center
now and then, aren't you?

00:09:35.241 --> 00:09:37.577 position:50% align:center
Hi there, the name's Sakaki.
I'm a junior, too.

00:09:37.660 --> 00:09:39.454 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Hana Uzaki, sophomore!

00:09:39.537 --> 00:09:41.247 position:50% align:center
Sakurai is a hardcore gloomlord,

00:09:41.331 --> 00:09:43.500 position:50% align:center
but I hope you guys have
fun together, anyway.

00:09:43.583 --> 00:09:45.418 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Will you please get outta here?

00:09:45.502 --> 00:09:47.212 position:50% align:center
Listen I don't want
you to worry.

00:09:47.295 --> 00:09:50.256 position:50% align:center
I'll promise I'll still keep
hanging out with you.

00:09:50.340 --> 00:09:53.093 position:50% align:center
So? Where are we gonna
go after class today?

00:09:53.176 --> 00:09:54.844 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Why are you saying
that as if my schedule's

00:09:54.928 --> 00:09:56.346 position:50% align:center
already booked?

00:09:56.429 --> 00:09:59.182 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] Huh? Cuz I said I wanted
to hang out at your place!

00:09:59.265 --> 00:10:00.892 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
You want to come over again?

00:10:00.975 --> 00:10:02.352 position:50% align:center
Well, think about it.

00:10:02.435 --> 00:10:04.187 position:50% align:center
If you're always hanging out
with your one male friend,

00:10:04.270 --> 00:10:05.855 position:50% align:center
people are definitely
gonna talk.

00:10:05.939 --> 00:10:08.024 position:50% align:center
I mean, you guys'll be
fan art before you know it.

00:10:08.108 --> 00:10:10.151 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Who exactly are
you worried about, anyway?

00:10:10.235 --> 00:10:12.028 position:50% align:center
Who cares what
other people think?

00:10:12.112 --> 00:10:14.781 position:50% align:center
Also, your random assumption
that I only have one male friend

00:10:14.864 --> 00:10:16.157 position:50% align:center
is pretty freakin' stupid.

00:10:16.241 --> 00:10:18.785 position:50% align:center
Come on, don't feel like
you have to show off, now.

00:10:18.868 --> 00:10:19.911 position:50% align:center
What? I'm not!

00:10:19.994 --> 00:10:21.871 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI]
So that's how it is...

00:10:21.955 --> 00:10:23.123 position:50% align:center
[school bell rings]

00:10:23.206 --> 00:10:25.959 position:50% align:center
Uh-oh. That's my cue!
Off to class! See ya!

00:10:26.042 --> 00:10:27.627 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
No you won't.

00:10:29.254 --> 00:10:30.296 position:50% align:center
