00:19:25.206 --> 00:19:27.334 position:50% align:center
This is a little much.

00:19:27.417 --> 00:19:30.628 position:50% align:center
Well. It's not that I hate it.

00:19:30.712 --> 00:19:33.465 position:50% align:center
I could just never
handle mint as a kid.

00:19:33.548 --> 00:19:35.925 position:50% align:center
So, anything with that
cooling sensation...

00:19:36.009 --> 00:19:38.345 position:50% align:center
Gum, cough drops... forget it.

00:19:38.428 --> 00:19:41.056 position:50% align:center
To this day I even use
non-mint toothpaste.

00:19:41.139 --> 00:19:43.433 position:50% align:center
But the cooling sensation's
the best part!

00:19:43.516 --> 00:19:45.769 position:50% align:center
With the sweet chocolate chaser?
I mean, are you kidding me?

00:19:45.852 --> 00:19:47.479 position:50% align:center
That's the whole thing
about choco-mint!

00:19:47.562 --> 00:19:48.813 position:50% align:center
What is wrong with you?

00:19:48.897 --> 00:19:51.358 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Anyway, since I
can't seem to do mint.

00:19:51.441 --> 00:19:54.861 position:50% align:center
I'll admit, I haven't
tried choco-mint.

00:19:54.944 --> 00:19:57.864 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Uh... Wha--

00:19:57.947 --> 00:19:59.824 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI yells]

00:19:59.908 --> 00:20:01.117 position:50% align:center
You're one of them!

00:20:01.201 --> 00:20:03.370 position:50% align:center
Those who dare to mock
choco-mint untasted

00:20:03.453 --> 00:20:05.330 position:50% align:center
like utter fools! You turd!

00:20:05.413 --> 00:20:09.084 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] All right!
I'm sorry, okay? I'm sorry!

00:20:09.167 --> 00:20:10.335 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI sighs]

00:20:10.418 --> 00:20:14.464 position:50% align:center
I get it. It all stems
from childhood trauma.

00:20:14.547 --> 00:20:16.424 position:50% align:center
But you should be
good to go, now.

00:20:16.508 --> 00:20:19.302 position:50% align:center
I mean, it's not like you're
a child anymore, so...

00:20:19.386 --> 00:20:20.845 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:20:20.929 --> 00:20:23.181 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] They do say your
sense of taste changes

00:20:23.264 --> 00:20:24.015 position:50% align:center
as you grow up.

00:20:24.099 --> 00:20:26.059 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Maybe, I dunno.

00:20:26.142 --> 00:20:28.603 position:50% align:center
You wanna try one, just to see?

00:20:28.687 --> 00:20:30.647 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Uh... Rgh...

00:20:30.730 --> 00:20:32.524 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Why the hesitation?

00:20:32.607 --> 00:20:36.027 position:50% align:center
You'll be fine, I promise it's
not too intense or anything.

00:20:36.111 --> 00:20:38.363 position:50% align:center
What? Are you really scared?

00:20:38.446 --> 00:20:39.489 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:20:39.572 --> 00:20:42.283 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
C'mon, you can do it!

00:20:42.367 --> 00:20:43.952 position:50% align:center
Conquer your bias.

00:20:44.035 --> 00:20:45.620 position:50% align:center
Mint's not scary.

00:20:45.704 --> 00:20:47.997 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
No, but your eyes sure are!

00:20:50.750 --> 00:20:53.253 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Look, just eat it already.

00:20:53.336 --> 00:20:55.964 position:50% align:center
All right, fine. Here goes.

00:20:56.047 --> 00:20:59.300 position:50% align:center
Great! See? Now just say, "ah!"

00:21:01.261 --> 00:21:03.596 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Now that I think
about it, isn't this...

00:21:06.182 --> 00:21:07.767 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
...an indirect kiss?

00:21:07.851 --> 00:21:10.353 position:50% align:center
Now her silliness is
rubbing off on me!

00:21:11.438 --> 00:21:12.939 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
But if I don't eat this now,

00:21:13.023 --> 00:21:15.400 position:50% align:center
it'll turn into a
whole thing again.

00:21:15.483 --> 00:21:18.528 position:50% align:center
Couldn't she be a little more
mindful of this crap?

00:21:28.246 --> 00:21:30.040 position:50% align:center
Verdict?

00:21:30.123 --> 00:21:34.919 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI sighs]
It's actually... tasty, I'd say.

00:21:35.003 --> 00:21:37.005 position:50% align:center
That's kind of a vague answer.

00:21:37.088 --> 00:21:39.758 position:50% align:center
But at least you did
manage to try it!

00:21:39.841 --> 00:21:41.718 position:50% align:center
Last one's mine!

00:21:44.429 --> 00:21:45.347 position:50% align:center
Uh.

00:21:45.430 --> 00:21:46.639 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Huh?

00:21:48.975 --> 00:21:51.061 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI groans]

00:21:51.144 --> 00:21:53.605 position:50% align:center
Oh. I'm sorry.

00:21:53.688 --> 00:21:56.232 position:50% align:center
Uh. What for?

00:21:56.316 --> 00:22:00.570 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI grunts]
Nothing. Forget it.

00:22:00.653 --> 00:22:04.240 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Now? You realize it now?

00:22:04.324 --> 00:22:06.034 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI] Look, it'll take a
thousand years for them

00:22:06.117 --> 00:22:07.952 position:50% align:center
to get together on their own!

00:22:09.788 --> 00:22:12.457 position:50% align:center
Then I guess I'll have to
live a thousand years!

00:23:46.051 --> 00:23:48.511 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI] I will get
you two together, Saku!

00:23:48.595 --> 00:23:49.929 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI sighs]